DDI-DrugBank.d489.s1|0-144|Concomitant administration of Kerlone with the oral anticoagulant warfarin has been shown not to potentiate the anticoagulant effect of warfarin.|drug
DDI-DrugBank.d489.s1|146-286|However, in patients receiving warfarin, the anticoagulant effect should be monitored closely, and the dose of warfarin adjusted accordingly.|drug
DDI-DrugBank.d489.s1|288-396|It is recommended that the initial dose of warfarin be reduced by 25% when initiating treatment with Kerlone.|drug
DDI-DrugBank.d489.s1|398-497|Once the anticoagulation profile is established, the dose of warfarin can be increased if necessary.|drug
DDI-DrugBank.d489.s1|499-682|For patients on long-term anticoagulation therapy, the dose of warfarin should be adjusted according to the international normalized ratio (INR) obtained from the patient’s blood test.|drug
DDI-DrugBank.d489.s1|684-853|When discontinuing treatment with Kerlone, the anticoagulant effect of warfarin should be monitored frequently until the anticoagulant effect returns to the normal range.|drug
