DDI-DrugBank.d320.s3|0-371|Although no clinical studies have been conducted, it is likely that the metabolism of levobupivacaine may be affected by the known CYP3A4 inhibitors (such as phenytoin, phenobarbital, rifampin), CYP3A4 inducers (such as carbamazepine, phenothizines, protease inhibitors, and saquinavir), and CYP3A4 substrates (such as amiodarone, cyclosporine, fluoxetine, and nelfinavir)|drug
DDI-DrugBank.d320.s3|372-450|However, if this drug is used, the metabolism of levoamiodarone may be affected|drug_n
DDI-DrugBank.d320.s3|451-671|It is also important to note that the metabolism of levoamiodarone may be affected by the following drugs: amiodarone, cimetidine, dexamethasone, fluoxetine, indinavir, omeprazole, ranitidine, sotalol, and thyroid hormone|drug
